      <pubDate>Thu, 13 Aug 2015 23:08:32 +0200</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://www.pitslamp.com/blog/20150813_pitslamp_short_after_the_storm/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://www.pitslamp.com/images/blogposts/20150813_thunderstorm-9400.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Mal√©ves-Sainte-Marie-Wastines after the thunderstorm&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Like a lot of photographers, I went outside into the thunderstorm to try and make some lightning shots. This time I did not manage to capture anything useful, that&amp;rsquo;ll be for next time, when I&amp;rsquo;m better prepared.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://www.pitslamp.com/images/blogposts/20150813_thunderstorm-9404.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Hay drying&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As you can see in the photos above I managed to capture a rather interesting photo afterwards when the thunderstorm had passed and the rain was evaporating under a pastel sunset.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
